sentences: Robert Hood (born 1965 in Detroit, Michigan) is an American electronic music producer and DJ.
In 1994, Hood founded the minimal techno label M-Plant in Detroit.
In 1992, Hood left Detroit and Underground Resistance with Jeff Mills to create a series of recordings both as H&M and X-103.
